The paper proposes an approach to continual deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The approach leverages deep model compression, critical weights selection, and progressive networks expansion, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image classification tasks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of lifelong learning, which is a topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a topic in the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
